with what money?

94
00:06:04,531 --> 00:06:07,400
What? But I stayed up
all night to make...

95
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,102
...this mix tape for the trip.

96
00:06:09,102 --> 00:06:10,604
God, how old are you?

97
00:06:10,604 --> 00:06:12,272
It's not like you're going
on your first drive

98
00:06:12,272 --> 00:06:14,574
after being dateless
for 30 years.

99
00:06:14,941 --> 00:06:18,545
Besides, cassette tape players
aren't built in cars anymore.

100
00:06:18,545 --> 00:06:20,981
I worked really hard to make
"My Best Music" tape.

101
00:06:20,981 --> 00:06:22,015
We don't have time.

102
00:06:22,015 --> 00:06:23,183
‐Let's go.
‐But wait, Gin!

103
00:06:23,183 --> 00:06:24,351
