104
00:06:24,351 --> 00:06:27,220
The thing is, we can't even
afford to buy a train ticket.

105
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:28,855
Can't you understand?

106
00:06:29,522 --> 00:06:31,157
But then, how are we going to...?

107
00:06:31,157 --> 00:06:32,993
We're going to jump the gate,
aren't we?

108
00:06:32,993 --> 00:06:34,894
We have to cheat
on the train fare!

109
00:06:34,894 --> 00:06:36,730
No way, because that's a crime!

110
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:38,898
How about buying
discount fares at least?

111
00:06:38,898 --> 00:06:39,833
We have no choice then.

112
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:41,201
We'll just have
to take a taxi.

113
00:06:41,201 --> 00:06:44,037
Hey! Do you have some serious
hearing problems or what?

114
00:06:44,037 --> 00:06:46,006
‐How do we pay?
‐How about this?

115
00:06:46,006 --> 00:06:47,040
I have an idea.

116
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:49,276
Let's just borrow
one of those up there.

117
00:06:52,579 --> 00:06:53,613
I give up.

118
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:56,016
I don't think
we'll even get probation.

119
00:06:56,016 --> 00:06:57,550
I don't know what to do.

120
00:06:57,550 --> 00:06:59,052
Oh, well, you guys.

121
00:06:59,052 --> 00:07:01,288
You're all really
such a hopeless bunch.

122
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:03,356
You should all be
really thankful

123
00:07:03,356 --> 00:07:05,558
at least someone here
has some common sense.

124
00:07:06,993 --> 00:07:08,595
