like you has any money.

232
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:23,436
I bet your life must be as
tasteless as these noodles.

233
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:26,673
That's right, go ahead
and say it, tasteless.

234
00:13:30,209 --> 00:13:31,277
It's tasteless!

235
00:13:31,277 --> 00:13:32,111
Stop that!

236
00:13:32,111 --> 00:13:33,546
You can't just eat my noodles!

237
00:13:33,546 --> 00:13:34,781
You have to pay
for them first,

238
00:13:34,781 --> 00:13:36,482
and listen, I'm a man
of the sea.

239
00:13:36,482 --> 00:13:37,817
It's true I don't have
any money,

240
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:40,253
but I can give you something
just as valuable!

241
00:13:40,253 --> 00:13:43,656
Yeah? Then, I'm going
to need to see it first.

242
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:45,792
We'll get rid
of that alien after that.

243
00:13:52,465 --> 00:13:54,434
It's a pretty cool shirt,
though, Gin.

244
00:13:54,801 --> 00:13:55,968
Yeah, right.

245
00:13:55,968 --> 00:13:58,104
If my mother had worn
this shirt when I was a teenager,

246
00:13:58,104 --> 00:14:00,239
I would've disowned her
for it, you know.

247
00:14:01,007 --> 00:14:03,910
That shirt is very rare,
and it's not for sale.

248
00:14:03,910 --> 00:14:05,178
Only my staff can wear it.

249
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:07,080
Now you are all fellow men
of the sea!

250
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:08,147
So release me now!

251
00:14:08,147 --> 00:14:10,049
Men of sea don't do
this kind of thing!

252
00:14:10,049 --> 00:14:10,817
Let me go!

253
00:14:10,817 --> 00:14:11,884
Release me right now!

254
00:14:11,884 --> 00:14:13,886
Come on, I'm a man of the sea.
Come on.

255
00:14:13,886 --> 00:14:15,521
Hey, Gin, what are we going
to do now?

256
00:14:15,521 --> 00:14:16,956
Let me go,
I'm a man of the sea!

257
00:14:16,956 --> 00:14:18,858
‐I'm a man of the sea.
‐Okay.

258
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:20,626
We've got no choice
but to do it.

259
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:23,262
We have no choice
but to do what?

260
00:14:23,262 --> 00:14:26,933
You've got a deserted beach,
one alien in the water,

261
00:14:26,933 --> 00:14:28,668
and three beach samurai.

262
00:14:29,435 --> 00:14:31,104
Who will protect the beach
if we don't?

263
00:14:31,337 --> 00:14:33,206
When you're down,
how do you pick yourself up?

264
00:14:35,374 --> 00:14:37,577
People fall into two categories,

265
00:14:37,577 --> 00:14:39,612
depending on how
they pick themselves up.

266
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:41,647
The first kind of person
comforts himself

267
00:14:41,647 --> 00:14:44,083
by seeing somebody
who's worse off than he is.

268
00:14:47,687 --> 00:14:49,055
And then he thinks,

269
00:14:49,355 --> 00:14:51,657
"Hey, at least I'm better off
than that guy."

270
00:14:52,024 --> 00:14:54,327
And then there's the second
kind of person.

271
00:14:54,794 --> 00:14:57,563
He looks at something
much larger than himself

272
00:14:57,563 --> 00:14:59,432
and tries to raise
himself to it.

273
00:14:59,432 --> 00:15:02,034
I am one of those who belong
to the second group.

274
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:06,239
<i>Since the olden days,</i>
<i>whenever I've gotten into trouble,</i>

275
00:15:06,239 --> 00:15:07,907
<i>I always come to the ocean.</i>

276
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:10,443
<i>It helps me realize</i>
<i>how tiny I am.</i>

277
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:14,180
<i>I met my first wife, Hatsu,</i>
<i>at the ocean too.</i>

278
00:15:16,249 --> 00:15:17,850
<i>What I'm trying to say is,</i>

279
00:15:17,850 --> 00:15:21,120
it's like the sea is my textbook
and also my teacher.

280
00:15:23,256 --> 00:15:25,424
Everyone has some place
in their heart

281
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:27,527
where they can fall back
on when they need to.

282
00:15:27,860 --> 00:15:29,996
Even if I just drift
from job to job

283
00:15:29,996 --> 00:15:32,832
my heart will always
belong here, by the sea.

284
00:15:32,832 --> 00:15:34,467
And those jobs are the ways.

285
00:15:34,467 --> 00:15:36,803
I protect that place
where I have always belonged.

286
00:15:36,803 --> 00:15:38,104
It's not about the money.

287
00:15:38,104 --> 00:15:39,639
This job is my calling.

288
00:15:39,639 --> 00:15:41,941
Now do you finally understand...

289
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:44,277
what my true feelings
are about this?

290
00:15:50,383 --> 00:15:52,451
Are you really serious, sis?

291
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:55,388
I reached a settlement with
The Beach Community Association.

292
00:15:55,388 --> 00:15:57,790
If we get rid of the alien,
they'll give us something in return.

293
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:59,292
Hey, hey, please, listen to me.

294
00:15:59,292 --> 00:16:01,327
Then we gotta be fired up
to do this!

295
00:16:01,327 --> 00:16:03,462
‐My... my feelings.
‐Alright, let's go.

296
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:04,263
Right!

297
00:16:26,319 --> 00:16:28,321
But why do I have
to do this?

298
00:16:28,321 --> 00:16:29,755
Did I do something wrong?

299
00:16:29,755 --> 00:16:31,991
I was just cooking
fried noodles!

300
00:16:31,991 --> 00:16:34,927
Come on, give me a break,
I did nothing wrong!

301
00:16:34,927 --> 00:16:36,195
You guys, come on!

302
00:16:39,866 --> 00:16:40,766
Oh, man.

303
00:16:40,766 --> 00:16:42,668
My legs are wrinkly already.

304
00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:44,637
How am I supposed
to run like this

305
00:16:44,637 --> 00:16:48,140
when my legs are all soft
and wrinkly like this!

306
00:16:48,140 --> 00:16:49,842
It's not taking the bait.

307
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:53,546
I'm wondering if the alien is actually
not in this sea anymore.

308
00:16:54,714 --> 00:16:56,749
No, I don't think that's the case.

309
00:16:56,749 --> 00:16:58,484
The alien is still in this sea.

310
00:16:59,051 --> 00:17:00,353
I can feel it.

311
00:17:03,256 --> 00:17:05,458
<i>This alien is prepared</i>
<i>to fight us.</i>

312
00:17:06,392 --> 00:17:07,793
<i>A fight between men.</i>

313
00:17:08,461 --> 00:17:10,229
<i>Breathtaking offense and defense</i>

314
00:17:10,229 --> 00:17:13,032
<i>and the fulfillment</i>
<i>of a man's dreams!</i>

315
00:17:18,437 --> 00:17:20,172
<i>The alien must be staying low,</i>

316
00:17:20,172 --> 00:17:21,974
<i>just waiting for the right time!</i>

317
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:24,343
<i>This alien understands.</i>

318
00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:28,915
You understand how I feel,
don't you?

319
00:17:33,953 --> 00:17:36,656
Miss, do you understand
my feelings?

320
00:17:37,023 --> 00:17:38,658
Yes, I do.

321
00:17:38,658 --> 00:17:41,294
Oh, thank you so much,
Miss...

322
00:17:46,032 --> 00:17:48,434
Would you care to try
one of my omelets?

323
00:17:48,434 --> 00:17:50,536
I made them just this morning.

324
00:17:50,536 --> 00:17:51,704
Go on and try one.

325
00:17:55,942 --> 00:17:57,843
‐I'm not...
‐You can't fight an alien...

326
00:17:57,843 --> 00:17:59,245
...in the sea if you're hungry.

327
00:18:15,328 --> 00:18:16,362
How about another one?

328
00:18:16,362 --> 00:18:17,563
Go on and take one.

329
00:18:19,532 --> 00:18:20,733
I've had enough.

330
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,636
Miss, do you understand...

331
00:18:24,403 --> 00:18:25,471
how I feel?

332
00:18:25,838 --> 00:18:28,240
I only wish that
I could swim like them.

333
00:18:32,011 --> 00:18:33,813
I see.

334
00:18:33,813 --> 00:18:35,314
You're sensitive to the sun,

335
00:18:35,314 --> 00:18:37,850
so you can't go swimming
in the ocean.

336
00:18:37,850 --> 00:18:39,518
But it's best that
you're not out there.

337
00:18:39,952 --> 00:18:41,387
There's really no need
to hold back.

338
00:18:41,387 --> 00:18:43,189
The alien might appear
at any time.

339
00:18:43,189 --> 00:18:44,290
Are they alright?

340
00:18:46,392 --> 00:18:49,161
Oh, well, I guess If they can't listen
to a guy's story

341
00:18:49,161 --> 00:18:50,563
then, maybe they deserve to die.

342
00:18:52,164 --> 00:18:54,700
It must be so nice to swim.

343
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:55,735
Uhh... hey, Miss?

344
00:18:55,735 --> 00:18:57,336
What are you planning
to do with that?

345
00:18:57,336 --> 00:18:59,338
Where did you even find
that huge thing?

346
00:18:59,338 --> 00:19:01,540
I'd rather just
end their happiness

347
00:19:01,540 --> 00:19:03,909
than have to watch someone
other than me be happy.

348
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:07,213
Everyone, run away from here!

349
00:19:07,213 --> 00:19:08,581
This girl is really weird!

350
00:19:08,581 --> 00:19:10,449
She's completely crazy!

351
00:19:15,087 --> 00:19:17,156
Shoot! Now it's turned into
a double wammy!

352
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:19,859
Hey! Run away, you two!

353
00:19:19,859 --> 00:19:21,093
Everybody run!

354
00:19:21,394 --> 00:19:22,194
Double wammy!

355
00:19:22,194 --> 00:19:23,896
You're twice in deep shit!

356
00:19:24,997 --> 00:19:26,065
What's that?

357
00:19:26,065 --> 00:19:27,600
Double panties?

358
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,535
Did he forget
his swim trunks, maybe?

359
00:19:29,535 --> 00:19:30,403
Behind you!

360
00:19:30,403 --> 00:19:32,038
Shinpachi, behind you!

361
00:19:32,038 --> 00:19:34,440
Hey, Miss, you'd better wait
a bit with that rock.

362
00:19:36,542 --> 00:19:37,443
What's that?

363
00:19:49,255 --> 00:19:50,890
It's here!
Seriously!

364
00:19:50,890 --> 00:19:52,324
Like it's right here!

365
00:19:53,959 --> 00:19:54,693
Wait, wait, wait!

366
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:56,562
I can't go any faster!

367
00:19:58,364 --> 00:19:59,698
Wait, Shinpachi!

368
00:20:00,266 --> 00:20:01,834
How come you can
swim so fast?

369
00:20:01,834 --> 00:20:02,935
It's not like you!

370
00:20:02,935 --> 00:20:04,737
You're the character
who can't do anything right

371
00:20:04,737 --> 00:20:06,806
except set up my jokes, right?

372
00:20:07,506 --> 00:20:10,509
My eyes are popping out,
my eyes are popping out!

373
00:20:10,743 --> 00:20:12,078
You bastards!

374
00:20:13,012 --> 00:20:15,448
Thanks for treating me
like crap this entire time.

375
00:20:15,448 --> 00:20:18,617
But now I'll teach you
to fear a man of the sea!

376
00:20:18,617 --> 00:20:20,052
Aaah... It's coming!

377
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:21,654
They've teamed up somehow!

378
00:20:21,654 --> 00:20:23,055
Gin! Shinpachi!

379
00:20:23,055 --> 00:20:23,956
Kagura, quick!

380
00:20:23,956 --> 00:20:25,124
Hit them back
with that rock.

381
00:20:25,124 --> 00:20:26,025
All right.

382
00:20:29,695 --> 00:20:31,697
Miss, hold on there!
Wait, wait, wait!

383
00:20:31,697 --> 00:20:34,333
I'm on it! Look, I agree that you
should throw this rock,

384
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:35,468
but not when I'm on it.

385
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:37,603
There!

386
00:20:41,574 --> 00:20:42,441
Hey, that...

387
00:20:48,013 --> 00:20:49,381
Whoops, my bad.

388
00:20:53,552 --> 00:20:55,621
Hey, is everyone all right?

389
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:10,102
Eat me if you want to.

390
00:21:10,569 --> 00:21:12,505
Traveling across the oceans
inside your stomach

391
00:21:12,505 --> 00:21:14,140
doesn't sound too bad.

392
00:21:23,682 --> 00:21:25,084
You...

393
00:21:34,827 --> 00:21:36,195
So, that's the story.

394
00:21:38,230 --> 00:21:40,266
And I think he truly understood

395
00:21:40,266 --> 00:21:42,034
just how much
I loved the sea.

396
00:21:43,102 --> 00:21:45,104
It's not about the mind, though.

397
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:48,140
Men always speak out
with their souls.

398
00:21:49,875 --> 00:21:51,610
His appearance may have been
frightening,

399
00:21:51,610 --> 00:21:53,712
this is true,
but I'm pretty sure

400
00:21:53,712 --> 00:21:56,482
he just wanted to have
some fun with us, you know.

401
00:21:58,450 --> 00:22:00,085
Yeah, I am sure that was it.

402
00:22:00,085 --> 00:22:03,088
And I can tell because only
good people live in the sea.

403
00:22:06,025 --> 00:22:06,926
Soaking in the sea,

404
00:22:06,926 --> 00:22:09,662
makes all the dirt and
scum wash away.

405
00:22:12,731 --> 00:22:14,200
All the scum.

406
00:22:15,034 --> 00:22:16,869
There is a huge
bag of scum

407
00:22:16,869 --> 00:22:18,771
pictured in the
newspaper, though.

408
00:22:22,374 --> 00:22:24,009
Whatever, man.

409
00:23:57,936 --> 00:24:00,372
<i>There's a ghost in the</i>
<i>Shinsengumi headquarters?</i>

410
00:24:00,773 --> 00:24:02,141
<i>Don't be silly!</i>

411
00:24:02,474 --> 00:24:04,076
<i>There's no such thing in this world.</i>

412
00:24:04,376 --> 00:24:06,211
<i>Wait. No, no, no, no!</i>
<i>It does exist!</i>

413
00:24:07,079 --> 00:24:08,480
<i>Help me!</i>

414
00:24:09,315 --> 00:24:10,449
<i>The next episode ...</i>

415
00:24:12,284 --> 00:24:14,620
<i>Conveyor Belts!</i>

416
00:24:24,196 --> 00:24:27,466
Should I wear a different kimono
every once in a while?

